Heat the olive oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Add the onions and garlic and fry for two minutes, until soft.Add the spices and cook through for two more minutes.Add the tomato pur√©e, lentils, and vegetable stock. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to simmer for five minutes.Add the cream and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, pour the lentil curry into a warm bowl with the warm chipattis served on a plate alongside.